Put all the ingredients, except the oil, in a bowl and mix. Season with salt and pepper and set aside for 20 minutes.To cook the fritters, heat a little oil in a large frying pan over a medium heat. Take about 2 tablespoons of the mixture and shape into a patty, flatten slightly. Cook in batches for 2â€“3 minutes on each side until golden brown, adding more oil if necessary.Divide the fritters between serving plates. Serve with watercress and lemon wedges.